The paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms, specifically neural networks, for Structural Health Monitoring (SHM) of beam-like structures. The paper mentions the use of Bayesian Neural Networks (BNN), which falls under the category of probabilistic machine learning, making cs.LG the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) and Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) networks, which are commonly used in computer vision and sequence modelling tasks, respectively, making cs.CV and cs.SY likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of finite element analysis, which falls under the category of computational engineering, making cs.CE a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with damage detection and location identification, which falls under the category of control engineering, making cs.NE a likely sub-category.
